def s(n):
   for i in range(n,0,-1):
       if n%i == 0:
           return i

def main():
    n = int(input())
    t = input()
    d = s(n)
    print(t[d:], end=" ")
    print(t[:d][::-1], end=" ")

main()


n = int(input())
t = input()

# reverse the string
t = t[::-1]

for i in reversed(range(1, n + 1)):
    if n % i == 0:
        # reverse the substring
        t = t[:i][::-1] + t[i:]

print(t)

n = int(input("Enter the number of elements: "))

s = [0] * n

    s[i] = int(t[i])

print(s)

for i in range(n):
    for j in range(i + 1, n):
        if s[i] > s[j]:
            temp = s[i]
            s[i] = s[j]
            s[j] = temp

print(s)
